narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: GREAT professor. Work is very manageable. That said, if you're not into Russian literature or haven't taken another class in it, you should probably take his Tolstoy lecture first or the Dostoevsky class. I do think having a background in it helps. That said, I highly recommend the class!
Take it. But it is a very difficult course
This is a course in which you discover great books and discuss them. I definite recommend it.
